        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### What SRD-46 *does* have: Polypeptide Ligands\n\nThe database includes **98 polypeptide-class ligands** — short synthetic or natural peptides (typically 2–6 residues). These serve as excellent **model systems** for understanding metal–protein binding-site chemistry. A sample of well-studied polypeptides:\n\n| Ligand | Ligand ID | Metal Systems (VLM count) |\n|--------|-----------|--------------------------|\n| Tetraglycine (Gly₄) | ligand_6595 | 46 |\n| Fibrinopeptide A fragment | ligand_6692 | 12 |\n| L-Ala₄ | ligand_6597 | 10 |\n| Gly-Pro-Gly-Gly | ligand_6610 | 7 |\n| Gly-Sar-Gly-Gly | ligand_6606 | 7 |\n| L-Ala-L-Pro-L-Ala-L-Ala | ligand_6614 | 7 |\n\nThese peptides coordinate metals primarily through their **terminal amine**, **deprotonated amide nitrogens**, and **carboxylate** groups — the same donor-atom types relevant to metal–protein interactions.",
