      {
        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "### Relevance to Transferrin Chemistry\n\nWhile transferrin itself is absent, SRD-46 has extensive data for iron and other biologically relevant metals bound to small ligands that model protein binding sites:\n\n- **Individual amino acids** (glycine, histidine, cysteine, tyrosine — the key donor groups in transferrin's binding cleft)\n- **Siderophore-like chelators** (citrate, EDTA, desferrioxamine) commonly used in iron–transferrin competition studies\n- **Short peptides** (the 98 polypeptides above) that approximate the coordination environment of protein metal-binding sites",
